Words & Meanings

jurisprudence - the theory or philosophy of law

surmise - suppose that something is true without having evidence to confirm it

proclivity - a tendency to choose or do something regularly

diabolical - characteristic of the Devil / unpleasant

dastardly - wicked and cruel

onomatopoeia - the formation of a word from a sound associated with what is named (e.g. cuckoo, sizzle ).
the use of onomatopoeia for literary effect.

transcendental - relating to a spiritual realm.

Machiavellian - cunning in politics 

espouse - adopt or support / marry

elude - escape typically in a skilful or cunning way.

condescension/disdain - unworthy.

(Term)Emancipation - It is a legal process that gives a teenager who is 16 or older legal independence from his or her parents or guardians.


